'''Claus Krag''' (born April 21, 1943) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[educator]], [[historian]], and writer. He is a noted specialist in [[Old Norse]] philology and medieval Norwegian history. Krag earned his [[Cand.philol.]] in 1969. He is Professor of History at [[Telemark University College]]. <ref>[http://www.hit.no/nor/ansatte/sok?textSearch=&selectOrgUnit=AF%252FIKH&ShowAnsatte=+Utf%C3%B8r+s%C3%B8k+ Telemark University College: Ansatte ved Institutt for Kultur- og Humanistiske fag], accessed 2010-08-17 {{no icon}}</ref><ref>[http://www.hit.no/nor/content/view/full/11808/(size)/minst Telemark University College: Claus Krag] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130222180026/http://www.hit.no/nor/content/view/full/11808/(size)/minst |date=2013-02-22 }}, accessed 2010-08-17 {{no icon}}</ref>
